   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="edition" ana="#b1" xml:lang="grc" subtype="transcription" xml:id="elus0051.transcription" corresp="#elus0051.translation">
            <p>+ Ἀναπ<supplied reason="lost">άη</supplied>
               <lb/> ὁ μακάριος Σε<unclear>ρ</unclear>
               <lb/>γίος ἐν μηνὶ
                    <unclear>Δί</unclear>
               <lb/>ου ιϛʹ <expan>
                  <abbr>ἰνδ</abbr>
                  <ex>ικτιῶνος</ex>
               </expan> αʹ
                    <lb/> ἔτους υ<unclear>ϟβ</unclear>ʹ</p>
         </div>
         <div type="translation" ana="#b1" xml:id="elus0051.translation" corresp="#elus0051.transcription">
            <p>The blessed Sergius, went to rest on the 16th of Dios, 1st indiction, year
                    492.</p>
         </div>
      </body>
      <back>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>The stone is vertically chisel dressed. The surface on the right side of the stone has been weathered away. The date in the inscription refers to November 2, 597 CE.</p>
         </div>
